         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">18/11/93. ¶  ¶ Since you, highly esteemed friend, have worked on the Rubiaceae of South America, ¶  I would like to ask you to tell me whether the genus  ¶ Euosmia ¶  HBK. is permanent. J. Hooker knew...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="de">93.11.18</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="de">To Jean Müller</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="de">Conservatoire et Jardin botanique, Geneva.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="de">18/11/93.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Da Sie, hochgeehrter Freund, die Rubiaceen Süd-Amerikas bearbeitet haben, möchte ich Sie bitten, mir zu sagen, ob das Genus <name key="Euosmia">Euosmia</name> HBK. Bestand hat. J Hooker kannte es ja nur aus der Abbildung. Martius Fl. Brasiliana ist hier nicht vorhanden, ausgenommen einige wenige Theile in meiner Bibliothek.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ich fühle mich Ihnen wieder verpflichtet für lichenologische Druckschriften. Ihre Arbeitskraft bleibt ungeschwächt. Möchte doch, ehe solche im späten Herbst Ihres Lebens sinkt nur wenigstens eine Synopsis aller Lichenen der Erde von <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">Ihnen</hi>
               </seg> noch verlangen nach Ihren unvergleichlichen Erfahrungen.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">Sie ehrend, der Ihre</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="de">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">18/11/93.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Since you, highly esteemed friend, have worked on the <name key="Rubiaceae">Rubiaceae</name> of South America,<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>For example, J. Müller (1875).</p>
               </note> I would like to ask you to tell me whether the genus <seg style="font-style: italic; ">
                  <name key="Euosmia">Euosmia</name>
               </seg> HBK. is permanent. J. Hooker knew it just from the figure. Martius <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Flora Brasiliana</seg> is not available here, except some few parts in my library.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I again feel myself indebted to you for lichenological papers. Your capacity for work remains undiminished. But before it sinks in the late autumn of your life, I would just like to ask again at least for a synopsis of all lichens of the world by <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">you</hi>
               </seg> from your incomparable experiences.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">Respectfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; font-size: 10pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd. von Mueller.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Euosmia">Euosmia</name>
            </p>
            <p rend="plant%20names" xml:lang="en">
               <name key="Rubiaceae">Rubiaceae</name>
            </p>
